original_title: From Victoria Street to Ang Mo Kio
overview: This work documents a segment of Singapore’s education history –– the survival of the nation’s first Catholic missionary Chinese girls’ school through adversities during her formative years. It is a tribute to the arduous efforts and contributions of a generation of admirable educators who persevered in delivering the education of love with resilience and steadfastness.
tagline: Through the Generations: An Education of Love
title: From Victoria Street to Ang Mo Kio
